    "en": {
      "title": "The government bears the expenses of the quota",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Cabinet Spokesperson Bandula Gunawardena has said that the Sri Lankan government has paid for former President Gotabaya Rajapaksa's flight from Singapore to Thailand.",
        "He said the above while responding to a question raised by a journalist while participating in a press conference announcing the weekly cabinet decisions.",
        "He also said that former President Gotabaya Rajapaksa should be given all the bounties and special privileges enjoyed by the retired executive presidents and the wives of deceased former presidents as per the law."
      ],
